channel.title: Trouble setting up editors
channel.description:
I keep getting the following errors when I try to compile the starter project for the first time:
Error 1 struct: 'SplinePointData' conflicts with another type of the same name
Error 2 MSB3075 The command ""C:\Program Files\Unreal Engine - CSS\Engine\Build\BatchFiles\Build.bat" FactoryGameEditor Win64 Development -Project="C:\Users\<Username>\Documents\SatisfactoryMod1\StarterProject\FactoryGame.uproject" -WaitMutex -FromMsBuild" exited with code 5.
I've noticed that FSplinePointData.generated.h doesn't exist in the factorygame project.
Has anyone else had this problem. I followed the setup instructions precisely.

item.title: Trouble setting up editors
item.dc:creator: @Robb Rob B
item.description:
@Robb wrote:

I haven’t heard of this issue before, but there was an update pretty recently after all. I suggest you ask in the #help-making-mods channel on the Discord, which is usually where people will hang out and answer setup questions like this.
